# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Clockout — Phase 0 (Willingness-to-Pay validation) configuration
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. All vars are OPTIONAL: with none set, the page
# still runs and records signals locally (dev mode) — but to MEASURE real demand
# you must wire at least the waitlist endpoint + analytics.
# Vite only exposes vars prefixed with VITE_ to the client.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Where the email-capture form POSTs (JSON: {email, name, role, tier, intent}).
# Recommended: Google Sheets via Apps Script — see docs/google-sheet-capture.gs
# for the 5-minute setup, then paste the deployed /exec URL here. A script.google.com
# URL is auto-detected and posted in the no-cors mode Apps Script requires.
# (Formspree / Tally / custom JSON endpoints also work.) Empty = log to console only.
VITE_WAITLIST_ENDPOINT=""

# Stripe Payment Link for the refundable pre-pay (the STRONGEST WTP signal).
# Create at dashboard.stripe.com → Payment Links. Mark "fully refundable,
# charged at launch" in the product description. Leave empty to hide pre-pay.
VITE_STRIPE_PAYMENT_LINK=""

# Plausible analytics domain (e.g. "getclockout.com"). When set, the Plausible
# script loads and custom WTP events (email_signup, pro_click, prepay_click) fire.
VITE_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=""

# Honest baseline for the "Join N reclaiming their evenings" counter.
# Start at 0. Bump manually as REAL signups land in your backend (per the
# Phase 0 playbook §2.1 — never fabricate). Session signups add on top live.
VITE_WAITLIST_BASE="0"
